02:14.453 --> 02:15.921
Hey, there's Ms. Carol.

02:15.948 --> 02:17.789
Go get her. Go get her.

02:19.259 --> 02:22.082
Ms. Carol. Ms. Carol!

02:22.342 --> 02:24.955
Good morning, Markell. Come here.

02:26.661 --> 02:28.368
Ooh, what's this?

02:28.394 --> 02:29.735
- Oh, be careful.
- Whoa, whoa.

02:29.767 --> 02:30.967
- It's a globe.
- Markell.

02:30.992 --> 02:32.130
Markell.

02:32.638 --> 02:34.670
What did I tell you about asking first?

02:34.723 --> 02:36.205
Can I touch it, please?

02:36.238 --> 02:37.931
It's not for touching unless
our hands are clean.

02:37.958 --> 02:39.312
- They are.
- They are?

02:39.344 --> 02:40.779
I washed them after breakfast. Good.

02:40.813 --> 02:42.481
- I always do.
- Look.

02:42.515 --> 02:45.047
Listen to Ms. Carol, okay?
Be good today.

02:45.072 --> 02:47.168
- Bye, Daddy.
- Bye, Dante.

02:47.827 --> 02:49.622
Can we paint today, Ms. Carol?

02:49.655 --> 02:51.798
Well, I was going to share
the globe with the class...

02:51.823 --> 02:52.958
If we're good? Please?

02:52.992 --> 02:54.777
I want to paint you another picture.

02:54.844 --> 02:56.923
Remember the tree I painted for you?

02:56.970 --> 02:59.699
I certainly do. It was
a beautiful tree.

02:59.927 --> 03:01.709
There's the warning bell,
though, so we better hurry.

03:01.733 --> 03:05.197
I'm excited for school today,
especially if we paint.

03:05.270 --> 03:06.539
We'll see.

03:06.572 --> 03:08.373
We'll see, which means <i>maybe.</i>

03:08.398 --> 03:09.708
- We'll see!
- We'll see, okay.

03:09.742 --> 03:11.444
And we are calming down.

03:11.476 --> 03:12.678
We are calming down.

03:12.703 --> 03:13.880
Yeah, well see!

03:29.462 --> 03:31.530
- Hey.
- Hey.

03:31.564 --> 03:33.565
- Want to...
- Yeah.

03:37.403 --> 03:39.071
Yeah, yeah.

03:39.131 --> 03:40.566
Yeah, I know how Pete works.

03:40.629 --> 03:42.675
He's gotta cross the routine stuff off

03:42.708 --> 03:44.737
one by fucking...

03:44.943 --> 03:46.344
- Excuse me.
- It's cool.

03:46.758 --> 03:48.815
The chief is very, very methodical.

03:49.133 --> 03:50.683
He don't make leaps, but sometimes,

03:50.717 --> 03:54.754
ironically, being too careful,
he misses opportunities.

03:54.952 --> 03:56.309
That was your conflict?

03:56.334 --> 03:57.923
Conflict?

03:57.957 --> 04:00.026
We didn't have a conflict.
We had arguments.

04:00.058 --> 04:01.617
Most days, we cleared the office.

04:01.642 --> 04:04.097
Folks ran like the
building was on fire.

04:04.130 --> 04:06.332
Hmm. So that's why you quit.

04:06.809 --> 04:09.557
Nah. I liked talking to him.

04:10.619 --> 04:11.904
What the hell?

04:11.938 --> 04:13.387
Huh, when did this happen?

04:13.420 --> 04:14.502
You haven't seen this?

04:14.527 --> 04:15.633
Kind of cool. It's just a pop-up.

04:15.658 --> 04:17.159
My mama used to get her
hair done here. Hmm.

04:17.510 --> 04:18.688
So, you got any leads?

04:18.713 --> 04:20.944
I mean, other than
Pete sat on his hands,

04:20.969 --> 04:23.416
hoping someone's blood lights
up on the FBI database.

04:24.447 --> 04:26.822
Mr. Noveer, it was nice
of you to call me.

04:26.875 --> 04:29.488
I appreciate your wanting
to, whatever, mentor me.

04:29.522 --> 04:30.690
I sure know what it's like being

04:30.722 --> 04:32.392
the one black cop in the department.

04:32.424 --> 04:34.794
But I can't tell you details
of the investigation.

04:35.146 --> 04:37.590
Cool. Let's take in some culture.

04:47.295 --> 04:49.121
So, come on, clues out of the bag.

04:49.327 --> 04:51.611
What was the one detail?

04:52.107 --> 04:54.026
Part of the shipment was
cancelled at the last minute.

04:54.059 --> 04:55.615
Mr. Carl said the specs were off.

04:56.414 --> 04:58.084
- Okay.
- Don't they check the specs

04:58.116 --> 04:59.289
way earlier than the last minute,

04:59.314 --> 05:00.969
like, before it's packed?

05:01.262 --> 05:03.056
Smart. You tell that to Trask?

05:04.455 --> 05:06.393
Didn't think it was my place.

05:09.628 --> 05:11.630
Hey, Toni.

05:13.621 --> 05:15.101
Look.

05:15.534 --> 05:17.803
A young black cop can't
wait, can't do the routine.

05:18.036 --> 05:19.336
You gotta show initiative.

05:19.361 --> 05:20.839
I can't search the mill by myself.

05:20.873 --> 05:22.967
No, but here's the bind you're in.

05:23.047 --> 05:25.549
If you just do the routine,
they'll say you're lazy.

05:25.777 --> 05:27.813
And if you grab your chances
and show initiative,

05:27.846 --> 05:29.649
you'll piss some of them off.

05:29.788 --> 05:31.883
But if you impress Pete, he's fair.

05:32.502 --> 05:33.719
He'll reward you.

05:33.753 --> 05:35.421
If that's true, why'd you quit?

05:36.956 --> 05:38.825
That wasn't really Pete's fault or mine.

05:39.071 --> 05:40.347
Whose was it?

05:40.573 --> 05:41.869
History's.

05:42.207 --> 05:44.710
Look, gotta go.

05:50.509 --> 05:52.148
Will this, uh, cover everything?

05:52.201 --> 05:54.140
- That'll do it.
- All right, well, night or day,

05:54.173 --> 05:55.806
you text me if you hear anything.

05:55.832 --> 05:57.709
Mr. Furlbee, I have the...

05:58.519 --> 05:59.960
Don't worry about me, young man.

06:00.006 --> 06:01.206
I'm just leaving.

06:03.025 --> 06:04.387
You play Monopoly as a kid?

06:04.412 --> 06:05.818
Oh. No, no,

06:05.851 --> 06:08.488
these are supposed to
be glued down, right?

06:08.907 --> 06:10.108
Uh...

06:10.782 --> 06:13.391
Now, see, the orange is all me.

06:13.424 --> 06:14.972
Mm.

06:14.997 --> 06:16.218
You got 'em surrounded.

06:16.411 --> 06:17.529
Yeah.

06:17.784 --> 06:20.682
I don't know which way this goes.

06:20.707 --> 06:22.052
This front or the back?

06:22.077 --> 06:23.276
Um, sorry.

06:23.310 --> 06:25.508
- I didn't mean to interrupt.
- Uh, no, no problem.

06:25.659 --> 06:27.344
- Is he a client, or...
- He's just someone I got some

06:27.369 --> 06:28.513
private, uh, business with.

06:28.538 --> 06:30.217
- That the bank paperwork?
- Yes.

06:30.522 --> 06:33.485
I'm sure you took a look at what
the loan extension is for?

06:33.567 --> 06:34.835
- All of this?
- Well,

06:34.860 --> 06:36.031
with everything that's
going on right now,

06:36.055 --> 06:37.143
we have to be a little aggressive.

06:37.167 --> 06:39.541
I mean, look at everything
that's not orange.

06:44.865 --> 06:46.300
<i>You ready to watch?</i>

06:46.325 --> 06:48.039
- Yes.
- You ready to listen?

06:48.088 --> 06:49.922
- Yes.
- You ready to think?

06:49.947 --> 06:51.916
Yes.

06:52.018 --> 06:53.307
What does this say?

06:53.359 --> 06:54.694
- Box.
- Box!

06:54.966 --> 06:57.784
"B" is for box. Who's got a "B"?

06:57.825 --> 06:59.246
- Ooh! Ooh!
- Do you have a box? Good.

06:59.279 --> 07:00.642
- Box? Box?
- Ooh, I do!

07:00.667 --> 07:02.449
- I-I have box.
- Box?

07:02.862 --> 07:04.976
Read, look at it carefully.

07:05.104 --> 07:06.189
See how that loops?

07:06.214 --> 07:08.329
The E doesn't loop like that. Okay?

07:08.396 --> 07:09.863
Next.

07:10.577 --> 07:12.745
"K." What is it for?

07:12.872 --> 07:14.674
- For karate...
- Karate!

07:14.815 --> 07:17.639
I don't do karate. I do kung fu!

07:17.664 --> 07:19.300
You can do kung fu

07:19.325 --> 07:20.907
at recess, okay?

07:20.987 --> 07:23.290
For now, we're gonna sit down.

07:23.517 --> 07:25.085
Markell, I like it when you sit.

07:25.110 --> 07:26.828
- I like it when you sit.
- If we do a good job,

07:26.853 --> 07:28.149
can we have extra recess?

07:28.174 --> 07:30.396
You're doing a good job, and so, yes,

07:30.421 --> 07:31.704
we can have extra recess.

07:31.729 --> 07:33.698
I don't want extra recess.

07:33.894 --> 07:35.695
I wanna paint.

07:36.108 --> 07:38.462
Who else has got "K" for Kara...

07:38.487 --> 07:41.068
Markell, I like it when you sit down.

07:41.314 --> 07:44.162
Markell, what did I say about
touching the supplies?

07:44.839 --> 07:46.135
Look, Ms. Carol,

07:46.160 --> 07:47.789
- I'm putting it back.
- Good.

07:47.814 --> 07:49.882
Does that mean we can paint later?

07:49.907 --> 07:51.260
If I live that long.

07:51.285 --> 07:52.845
Come here. Come here.

07:52.899 --> 07:55.235
Take my hand, take my
hand, take my hand.

07:55.502 --> 07:56.904
Take my hand.

07:57.524 --> 08:01.036
Sit down, okay? Sit down quietly.

08:01.107 --> 08:03.576
Gently? Okay, good, go.

08:03.670 --> 08:05.294
Markell, what did we say?

08:05.364 --> 08:06.933
Quietly and gently.

08:07.452 --> 08:09.716
Sit! Very good.

08:09.750 --> 08:11.752
Now I'm happy.

08:12.525 --> 08:14.579
"Y" is for...

08:14.604 --> 08:16.507
- Yoga.
- Yoga!

08:16.567 --> 08:18.348
So, Toni, what did you find out?

08:18.373 --> 08:20.729
- Who the hell is Travis Wilcox?
- Age 38.

08:20.754 --> 08:23.075
Lives alone, owns a used
car lot on Highway 42.

08:23.155 --> 08:25.390
Are you talking about the guy
that Walmart was talking about?

08:25.415 --> 08:27.057
The one who bought all the shovels?

08:27.082 --> 08:29.117
Yeah, that's right, I talked
to a salesman at his car lot.

08:29.142 --> 08:32.011
He said Travis hasn't called in
or shown up since Seven Bloods.

08:32.292 --> 08:34.634
Huh. Has anybody else, uh,
reported him missing?

08:34.659 --> 08:37.332
- No.
- Aw, he's not missing, Chief.

08:37.385 --> 08:39.826
He's just exhausted from
digging a seven-person grave.

08:41.553 --> 08:43.717
Wilcox is a member of
American Forefront.

08:43.743 --> 08:44.928
They're a white supremacist group.

08:44.952 --> 08:46.922
Ah, okay, so that's
why you give a shit.

08:46.947 --> 08:48.648
- That's not why...
- Oh, don't...

08:48.673 --> 08:50.620
Don't get yourself all like,.

08:50.645 --> 08:52.030
You're right, they're nutjobs.

08:52.842 --> 08:54.429
I know him, Chief.

08:54.518 --> 08:56.684
He is a nut. Came in a year ago,

08:56.725 --> 08:57.752
saying there were Mexicans living

08:57.777 --> 08:58.969
in the woods behind his house.

08:59.025 --> 09:00.080
And if we didn't take care of them,

09:00.104 --> 09:01.013
he was gonna go "hunting wetbacks."

09:01.078 --> 09:03.130
- Hmm.
- I checked gun stores in Braden

09:03.155 --> 09:05.867
and Riverside, he's bought 22
different assault weapons.

09:05.910 --> 09:08.344
Seven .45's, four tactical shotguns...

09:08.424 --> 09:09.605
Here's the full printout, Chief.

09:09.630 --> 09:11.259
Come to think of
it, he had this crazy theory

09:11.283 --> 09:13.017
that Carl Steel was using illegals

09:13.050 --> 09:15.085
to work secret shifts at night.

09:15.206 --> 09:16.857
You know, taking jobs
away from Americans.

09:16.882 --> 09:19.814
If the Seven Bloods victims
were undocumented, sir...

09:19.927 --> 09:22.113
well, no one would report them missing,

09:22.138 --> 09:24.799
and they wouldn't show up
on the FBI's DNA database.

09:26.364 --> 09:28.999
Okay. So you're not totally worthless.

09:30.560 --> 09:31.675
Good work.

09:32.894 --> 09:34.386
Let's go check this out.

09:38.669 --> 09:41.029
You're not actually gonna go, are you?

09:41.338 --> 09:43.202
I don't know, I figured I
could learn more about him

09:43.227 --> 09:45.030
by working for him.

09:45.183 --> 09:47.953
Yeah, that's a really great idea.

09:47.986 --> 09:50.276
Go work for the guy who
might've killed seven peeps,

09:50.301 --> 09:53.575
and if he kills you, then
hey, you'll know he's a killer.

09:53.952 --> 09:56.154
How did he not recognize you?

09:56.596 --> 09:59.205
I don't know. I figured he would.

09:59.884 --> 10:02.175
But it was dark, and it
all happened so fast.

10:02.200 --> 10:04.155
You've never babysat before.

10:04.268 --> 10:06.136
Yeah, how hard can it be?

10:08.427 --> 10:10.463
You think he's cute.

10:11.350 --> 10:13.317
That's what this is about.

10:18.397 --> 10:19.718
Hello?

10:21.005 --> 10:23.008
Yeah, yeah...

10:30.926 --> 10:32.728
Okay. Yeah.

10:32.883 --> 10:35.386
Uh, I'll see you then.

10:38.807 --> 10:40.472
You look totally freaked out.

10:40.546 --> 10:42.073
Who was that?

10:42.756 --> 10:46.343
Uh, you know the private
investigator from yesterday?

10:47.110 --> 10:49.113
That was him.

10:59.505 --> 11:01.073
The research is pretty clear, though.

11:01.132 --> 11:02.933
Some physical activity
throughout the day...

11:02.958 --> 11:05.161
But it gets complicated
in overpopulated schools.

11:05.186 --> 11:07.455
Well, sure, but we
don't have that problem here.

11:07.936 --> 11:09.667
You okay, Carol?

11:10.261 --> 11:13.564
Mm, absolutely. I'm
just a little tired.

11:13.704 --> 11:15.506
Out dancing too many nights in a row?

11:15.620 --> 11:17.220
That's it.

11:17.775 --> 11:19.711
Well, we could sit. You want to sit?

11:19.743 --> 11:21.470
All this talk about
physical activity...

11:21.495 --> 11:22.519
You girls keep talking.

11:22.544 --> 11:24.845
I think I'll step outside
and clear my head.

11:24.882 --> 11:26.149
You really okay, Carol?

11:26.181 --> 11:27.364
Yeah, I'm fine.

11:27.785 --> 11:29.054
How's your class?

11:29.440 --> 11:31.337
Fine. They're fine.

11:31.362 --> 11:33.899
That... I've got a little
boy who may have

11:33.924 --> 11:37.197
the worst case of ADHD
I've ever seen, but...

11:37.397 --> 11:39.106
20 years from now,
he'll invent something

11:39.131 --> 11:41.034
that changes the way life is lived.

11:42.437 --> 11:44.703
Yeah. Of course. You're right.

11:44.953 --> 11:46.737
Doesn't make it easy, though.

11:46.770 --> 11:48.767
Do you remember what you
told me last September?

11:48.801 --> 11:49.861
What was that?

11:49.886 --> 11:51.660
Well, when I had those twins,

11:51.770 --> 11:55.040
you said, step one: be exasperated.

11:55.287 --> 11:57.689
Step two: get over it.

12:00.578 --> 12:02.260
I better hurry.

12:10.433 --> 12:11.866
Hey...

12:12.676 --> 12:14.310
Are we meeting?

12:14.425 --> 12:16.558
- Uh, I don't...
- No, no.

12:16.628 --> 12:18.952
No, this is... way too public.

12:18.977 --> 12:21.213
But actually, do you
have about ten minutes?

12:21.238 --> 12:23.040
- Because I...
- I kind of got a...

12:23.065 --> 12:25.867
Right. Yeah, no. This is too risky.

12:25.924 --> 12:27.892
I'm gonna call you. Diner?

12:28.441 --> 12:29.694
- Sounds good.
- Great.

12:29.734 --> 12:31.138
All right.

12:38.829 --> 12:40.098
Ah.

12:40.177 --> 12:42.113
Sorry to keep you waiting.

12:42.459 --> 12:45.270
- No worries.
- I appreciate you taking the time.

12:46.317 --> 12:48.285
I used to be a cop.

12:48.447 --> 12:51.016
We always like to talk face-to-face.

12:51.108 --> 12:52.972
I wanted to talk cause...

12:53.971 --> 12:56.307
after I saw you at Mr.
Bennett's last night,

12:57.219 --> 13:00.222
I found out he hasn't used
his four-wheeler in weeks.

13:00.945 --> 13:02.714
Ty told you that?

13:03.475 --> 13:05.505
So I got to thinking...

13:06.050 --> 13:07.918
if he wasn't telling the truth,

13:08.424 --> 13:10.059
maybe you weren't either.

13:10.999 --> 13:14.411
No chance you and Ty were
together when he got banged up?

13:15.007 --> 13:18.672
What? While we were in the
middle of killing seven people?

13:18.697 --> 13:20.433
No, huh?

13:20.698 --> 13:23.538
Would've started small. Three at most.

13:23.588 --> 13:26.024
Smart. Cause less of a scene that way.

13:26.049 --> 13:27.516
Yeah, you get it.

13:27.541 --> 13:29.878
Well, even if you weren't
killing seven people...

13:30.127 --> 13:31.528
why were you at Ty's?

13:32.121 --> 13:34.124
We're friends.

13:34.559 --> 13:36.318
That through your dad?

13:37.314 --> 13:39.140
You sure you weren't
together when he got hurt?

13:39.203 --> 13:41.571
- Friend of mine at the emergency...
- Okay. Yeah.

13:43.695 --> 13:44.963
We were together.

13:44.988 --> 13:47.226
And I'm sorry we lied
about it, but it...

13:47.298 --> 13:48.753
You know.

13:49.513 --> 13:50.834
He works for my dad.

13:50.928 --> 13:52.563
And he got hurt how?

13:55.879 --> 13:57.685
We had a miscommunication.

13:57.710 --> 13:59.040
Sometimes known as a fistfight.

13:59.065 --> 14:00.406
I saw Mr. Bennett's face

14:00.431 --> 14:01.780
and I'm looking at your knuckles.

14:01.872 --> 14:03.875
They didn't give him that shiner.

14:08.026 --> 14:12.099
We watched a movie and then, um...

14:14.197 --> 14:16.355
We snuck into the country club.

14:16.882 --> 14:18.583
After hours.

14:18.957 --> 14:20.437
Go on.

14:22.760 --> 14:24.362
It got romantic.

14:24.846 --> 14:27.299
But there were missed
signals and he thought that,

14:27.326 --> 14:30.434
I wanted something that I... didn't.

14:30.752 --> 14:32.551
And I, I...

14:32.791 --> 14:34.492
I-I sort of tripped him.

14:34.684 --> 14:36.188
Accidentally, I didn't mean to,

14:36.213 --> 14:38.174
but he still hit his face on the table.

14:38.316 --> 14:39.717
Ouch.

14:39.756 --> 14:40.916
Yeah, you saw it.

14:40.941 --> 14:43.347
Hmm. I meant the missed signals.

14:43.749 --> 14:46.846
We realized it was just
one big misunderstanding.

14:47.198 --> 14:49.434
And you guys wouldn't
tell me this because...?

14:49.861 --> 14:53.190
Because you're a stranger
that showed up at our door.

14:55.360 --> 14:56.561
Yeah.

14:56.586 --> 14:57.896
All right, that's a fair point.

14:59.136 --> 15:00.338
But look...

